# Example Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values

# Google OAuth Configuration
# Get your client ID from: https://console.cloud.google.com/
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Strava API Configuration
# Get your credentials from: https://www.strava.com/settings/api
VITE_STRAVA_CLIENT_ID=your-strava-client-id
VITE_STRAVA_CLIENT_SECRET=your-strava-client-secret

# Setup Instructions:

# Google OAuth Setup:
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select existing one
# 3. Enable Google Identity API
# 4. Go to Credentials > Create Credentials > OAuth 2.0 Client IDs
# 5. Set application type to "Web application"
# 6. Add authorized JavaScript origins: http://localhost:5173, http://localhost:5175
# 7. Replace the VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID above with your actual client ID

# Strava API Setup:
# 1. Go to https://www.strava.com/settings/api
# 2. Create a new application
# 3. Set Authorization Callback Domain to: localhost
# 4. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret above
# 5. SECURITY WARNING: In production, handle client secret on backend only!
# 6. NEVER commit .env.local to version control!